## Why This Is Asked

Tests cross-context saga design with event sourcing, CQRS, and tenancy. It probes how compensation flows across multiple bounded contexts and how to ensure correctness under retries.

## Key Concepts

- Saga orchestration vs choreography
- Event-sourced cross-tenant aggregates
- Idempotent handlers using (tenantId, orderId)
- Compensation patterns: revert inventory, refund, notify

## Code Example

```javascript
// Minimal orchestrator snippet
class Orchestrator {
  handle(event) {
    switch(event.type) {
      case 'InventoryReserved':
        publish({ type:'PaymentCapture', orderId: event.orderId, tenantId: event.tenantId});
        break;
      case 'ShippingFailed':
        publish({ type:'Compensate', orderId: event.orderId, tenantId: event.tenantId, reason:'Shipping failed' });
        break;
    }
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test idempotent handlers across tenants?
- How do you evolve event schemas without breaking consumers?
